Role : Technical Content Writer
Minimum Experience : 5 Years

Requirements/Skillsets
This Technical &nbsp;&nbsp;Content Writer works across a highly visible program where the platform you &nbsp;&nbsp;will help to work on, will have a direct and positive impact to the millions &nbsp;&nbsp;of users of our products. &nbsp;When any of our customers download and &nbsp;&nbsp;install any of our software products, they will be touching the Delivery &nbsp;&nbsp;Platform you are helping to create content on. The technical content created &nbsp;&nbsp;will be referred to by developers and integrators across all product teams to &nbsp;&nbsp;create install experiences provided by this state-of-the-art Delivery &nbsp;&nbsp;Platform named On-Demand Installation Services (ODIS). External user &nbsp;&nbsp;facing content might need to be created on an as needed basis.

Responsibilities

  Develop content following our learning strategies, content standards &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;and ensuring globalization readiness. This can include online help, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;naming and terminology, new user experiences, UI content, feature &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;descriptions, instructional text and/or videos, structured learning, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;recent changes and error messages
  Review any documentation written by developers for ODIS features, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;keeping an emphasis that they are technically accurate and brings &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;clarity for our internal consumers
  Develop templates for release notes, following our release notes &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;content standards
  Review, suggest and help drive improvements for Delivery Platform &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;group’s existing internal documentation.
  Develop and use all types of content types (workflows / process &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;schematics / instructional videos / developer consoles) to simplify the &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;developer’s / integrator’s understanding of ODIS features
  Work closely with senior team members to understand key customer &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;requirements and stay informed of project changes
  Work effectively with product design and as a member of Agile scrum &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;teams to provide content to support new features and workflows
  Conduct technical reviews of content deliverables to ensure accuracy
  Monitor technical feedback from partner teams and modify/update &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;content as appropriate to correct errors, enhance clarity, and improve &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;usability
  Assist with the application of voice and tone standards &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;to improve usability and consistency.
  Conduct or coordinate production reviews to ensure &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the reliability of the content solution, including navigation, search &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;functions, links and playback quality of videos.

Responsibilities
Minimum Qualifications

  Some experience in technical communication, instructional design, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;digital learning solutions, or a related field
  BS/BA in Technical Writing, Human Computer Interaction, Information &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Architecture, Computer Science, or Communications
  Exceptional verbal, written and visual communication skills
  A portfolio demonstrating excellent instructional design skills and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;deliverables in a technical backdrop

The Ideal Candidate

  Ability to deliver high quality work on tight schedules
  Ability to execute in a fast-paced, agile environment
  Can distill complex technical ideas to their essence
  Ability to adjust to changing priorities
  Not afraid to express ideas, or change your mind when someone has a &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;better one
  Has a positive, can-do approach that invites collaboration
  Is a Great listener

